bunk_beachqq28@nwbeaches.name: bunk_beachQQ28
bunk_beachqq28@nwbeaches.examine: They look a bit hard, but you could sleep in them.

secret_beachqq22@nwbeaches.name: secret_beachQQ22
secret_beachqq22@nwbeaches.examine: The spiral stair leads up to a trap door.

east_beachqq11@nwbeaches.name: east_beachQQ11
east_beachqq11@nwbeaches.examine: You see more of the beach.

bed_secret@nwbeaches.name: bed_secret
bed_secret@nwbeaches.examine: Hmmm...there's a secret door underneath the bed.  Wonder what's under it?

objqq01@nwbeaches.name: objQQ01
objqq01@nwbeaches.desc[0]: A key in the shape of a figure-eight is here.

roof_beachqq21@nwbeaches.name: roof_beachQQ21
roof_beachqq21@nwbeaches.examine:
The paintings on the walls depict the great heroes and gods.  One of
the gods is fairly heavy-bellied and incredibly hairy, with a massive
beard.  Also among them are the great enemies and wrongdoers, such as
the evil Goddess Yochlol and the powerful evil Wizard Tharoecon.
roof_beachqq21@nwbeaches.desc[0]: There's some paintings hung on the walls.

objqq00@nwbeaches.desc[1]: There is a mahogney desk here, up against the east wall.
objqq00@nwbeaches.name: objQQ00
objqq00@nwbeaches.examine:
It looks as if any business the Lighthouse Keeper may need to do
is done here, at this desk.  It has a drawer in it and implements
for writing.
Looks like any other drawer you've seen before - knob and all.
objqq00@nwbeaches.desc[0]: There is a mahogney desk here, with an open drawer.

bed_beachqq26@nwbeaches.name: bed_beachQQ26
bed_beachqq26@nwbeaches.examine:
The beds all look comfortable, despite the fact that this is just
the servants' place.

throne_beachqq24@nwbeaches.name: throne_beachQQ24
throne_beachqq24@nwbeaches.examine:
It is large and very beautiful.  The carvings are mainly of animals and
magic beasts.
throne_beachqq24@nwbeaches.desc[0]: A child's throne sits in the corner.

stairs_beachqq25@nwbeaches.name: stairs_beachQQ25
stairs_beachqq25@nwbeaches.examine:
Made out of marble, and as all the rest of the lighthouse made primarily
for beauty and with great skill.

objqq02@nwbeaches.name: objQQ02
objqq02@nwbeaches.desc[0]: A cell key lies here in the dirt.

beachqq20@nwbeaches.title: Entryway - Lighthouse
beachqq20@nwbeaches.description:
You stand in a small chamber just inside the front door of the lighthouse.
Just south of these cramped stucco walls is the main living room of the
lighthouse.  You can hear and smell a crackling, warm fire in the fireplace,
a dog's contented panting, and the sound of a young lady's laughter from
the next room.

beachqq19@nwbeaches.title: Takker's Jetty at the Lighthouse
beachqq19@nwbeaches.description:
You stand at the entrance to the lighthouse, a solid oak door set
back into the rounded wall.  To your north, the jetty leads you
back to dry land.

beachqq08@nwbeaches.title: Sandy Beach
beachqq08@nwbeaches.description:
The beach continues it's way east toward what appears to be a coastal
town.  A large pier juts out into the sea, ships dot the horizon as far
out to sea as you can see from the town.  To your west you may continue
along the beach.

beachqq35@nwbeaches.title: End of the Rocky Path
beachqq35@nwbeaches.description:
You have come to the end of the rocky path you've been following
along the sea.  South of you is the start of the beach, west is a moss-
covered rock face, and to the north the way is impassable.

beachqq28@nwbeaches.title: Cell
beachqq28@nwbeaches.description:
This bleak cell hosts only an uncomfortable looking cot and small hole
in one corner for necessary functions.

beachqq32@nwbeaches.title: Rocky Path
beachqq32@nwbeaches.description:
You stand on a rocky beach path near the mouth of a cave.
The entrance to the cave must be at least thirty feet high and
just as wide.  It doesn't look as if anything could live there,
as the water from the sea laps right inside the cave, but then,
you never know.

beachqq10@nwbeaches.title: The Base of the Village
beachqq10@nwbeaches.description:
You stand at the edge of the sea shore staring at a huge rock formation
which could be described (sort of) as a plateau rising up out if the ocean
floor and holding a sizable village atop it.  To the north is the cliff
face you have been following, which happens to put an end to this path just a
little ways northeast from your current position.  West the path heads along
the beach for quite a long distance.

beachqq00@nwbeaches.title: Steps Leading Down to the Sea
beachqq00@nwbeaches.description:
You are on a long flight of steps cut into a cliff face.
Just ahead of you, the boardwalk looms, while below you,
the steps continue for what seems an eternity.

beachqq06@nwbeaches.title: Along the Beach
beachqq06@nwbeaches.description:
You stand on a beach which stretches east to west for as far as
your eyes can see.  Jumbles of rock and scree litter the way here,
making it so you must watch your step.  You notice a bit of wood,
partially buried in the sand of the beach here.
   West is more rocky beach, while east the way gets a bit more flat.

beachqq04@nwbeaches.title: The Base of the Steps
beachqq04@nwbeaches.description:
You stand at the bottom of a set of steps cut into the face
of the cliff here.  The beach runs along east to west here as far
as you can see.

beachqq05@nwbeaches.title: Along the Beach
beachqq05@nwbeaches.description:
You stand on a beach which stretches east and west from here.
The waves, not very large at this time, lap gently near your, making
patterns in the fine sand.  To the west you see a few rocks jutting
from the sand and sea.  East is flat beach to the horizon.

beachqq02@nwbeaches.title: On the Cliff Face
beachqq02@nwbeaches.description:
The stairs continue, however you are much closer to the
bottom than the top now.  There appears to be an opening in
the rock to your east.  Inside you can only see darkness,
so it is possible that it is simply a natural fissure, but
then again, who knows?

beachqq16@nwbeaches.title: Rocky Path
beachqq16@nwbeaches.description:
The path, still rocky and hard to navigate, continues along to the
east and west.  Directly east of you begins a jetty which hosts a
lighthouse at it's end.  West seems only to host more rocks and possibly
a cave or two.

beachqq01@nwbeaches.title: Down the Cliff-Face
beachqq01@nwbeaches.description:
The steps continue down toward the sea, or up to the crest
of the cliff, depending on the way you're heading.  It looks
as if there may be some sort of cave down from here.

beachqq25@nwbeaches.title: On the Spiral Staircase
beachqq25@nwbeaches.description:
You have begun a descent down into the Lower Reaches of the Lighthouse.
You wonder why the basement of this happy home would not only be called
the 'Lower Reaches', but also capitalized for a moment - and then you see
what lies below you.
Looking almost like a medieval torture chamber, you see a room all in stone,
a deep cavernous hole in the center of it.  What looks to be an operating
table is set to one side with tables covered in instruments of dissection
and bubbling vials close by.
Do you really wish to descend into that room and visit with the 'good'
Lighthouse Keeper?

beachqq09@nwbeaches.title: Sandy Beach
beachqq09@nwbeaches.description:
The beach slopes upwards, slowly, gently toward the town to your east
which sits on a huge plateau.  You can now hear the sounds of a great many
voices coming from that direction, however traffic along this beach is 
at a bare minimum, which is to say not at all.  There must be another
entrance into the town somewhere.  To your west, the beach continues into
the western horizon.

beachqq11@nwbeaches.title: Along a Rocky Beach
beachqq11@nwbeaches.description:
The way gets much too rocky here for you to continue along the water any
further.  You do however, notice a trail through the rocks which heads
southwest.

beachqq13@nwbeaches.title: Rocky Path
beachqq13@nwbeaches.description:
The path continues it's way in a southwesterly direction toward the
lighthouse, or you may head northeast toward a less cluttered-looking
beach.

beachqq17@nwbeaches.title: Takker's Jetty
beachqq17@nwbeaches.description:
The jetty heads south into the sea ending at a lighthouse.  All
along the way, fishermen try their luck.

beachqq21@nwbeaches.title: Main Living Area - Lighthouse
beachqq21@nwbeaches.description:
This large room looks as if it has spent many happy times in the
company of the Lighthouse Keeper and his family.  The dinner table
looks as if it always would have room for one more, the fire always
warm and comforting, and of course, Max would always be around to
play catch or get his ears scratched.
To the east, you see what looks to be one of the family's bedrooms,
the same to the west.  Both have doors, but both doors are wide open.
A spiral stairway leads up into the lighthouse top, where the Keeper
must spend a great deal of his time.

beachqq12@nwbeaches.title: Rocky Path
beachqq12@nwbeaches.description:
The path meanders it's way through the rocks on this littered beach.
In the distance, you can see a lighthouse out at the end of a jetty,
it's gentle light guiding sailors safely past this rocky area.

beachqq15@nwbeaches.title: Rocky Path at Takker's Jetty
beachqq15@nwbeaches.description:
The path continues east or west from you, depending which way you are
heading.  A jetty runs out into the sea to your south, a strong, bold
lighthouse at it's end.

beachqq14@nwbeaches.title: Rocky Path
beachqq14@nwbeaches.description:
The path runs east to west over jumbled rock and fine beach sand.  Just to
your west, you see a jetty running out into the ocean, a lighthouse at it's
end.  To the east the path curves it's way along the beach.

beachqq18@nwbeaches.title: Takker's Jetty
beachqq18@nwbeaches.description:
All along the jetty, men relax in the sun, sitting in comfortable niches
in the rocks where they can wile away their time telling tall tales
about 'the ones that got away', discussing politics, or every now and
then, doing some fishing.

beachqq24@nwbeaches.title: Lighthouse Keeper's Daughter's Bedroom
beachqq24@nwbeaches.description:
What a cute little room!  Twin bed with a pink down comforter, a
doll collection which even impresses you, and many other assorted
toys sit on shelves, all neatly stacked and color-coordinated.

beachqq36@nwbeaches.title: End of the Path
beachqq36@nwbeaches.description:
The path can go no farther.  The cliff face runs directly into the sea from
here, no longer leaving the little bit of beach that you have been enjoying
just west and south and here.  Strange that a path would end so abruptly at a
cliff without leading anywhere...  Oh well!

beachqq07@nwbeaches.title: Sandy Beach
beachqq07@nwbeaches.description:
You stand on a sandy beach which runs along the shore east to west.
To the east you can just barely make out the rooftops of a large city
which sits nestled in a cove on the shore of the ocean.  To your west
you see that the beach gets a bit rockier than where you currently stand.  
A set of steps lead up the cliff face just to the west of you.

beachqq30@nwbeaches.title: Cell
beachqq30@nwbeaches.description:
This bleak cell hosts only an uncomfortable looking cot and small hole
in one corner for necessary functions.

beachqq34@nwbeaches.title: In the Kracken's Den
beachqq34@nwbeaches.description:
Something seems wrong here, very wrong.  Something makes the
water move and not just in a small spot, ALL of the water is
moving from some kind of monstrous movement under the water.

beachqq22@nwbeaches.title: Lighthouse Keeper's Bedroom
beachqq22@nwbeaches.description:
A huge plush king size bed, four posted with satin drapes.  A mahoganey
dresser with a matching vanity desk and mirror.
This lighthouse keeper must be one heck of a guy!

beachqq03@nwbeaches.title: On the Steps
beachqq03@nwbeaches.description:
Nearing the bottom, you really begin to get a good whiff
of the clean sea air as a breeze ruffles your clothing.  You
begin to feel a bit better about your day - the sea can do
that to a person.

beachqq31@nwbeaches.title: Rocky Path
beachqq31@nwbeaches.description:
The path continues along the beach, over rocks and scree.
Your options are east or west.

beachqq33@nwbeaches.title: Cave Entrance
beachqq33@nwbeaches.description:
You realize that if you wish to explore the confines of this
cave, you will have to get wet.  As you stand looking into the
cold, wet, darkness of the cave, the idea of jumping into that
water just for the sake of exploring does seem a bit nutty.

beachqq23@nwbeaches.title: Light Room
beachqq23@nwbeaches.description:
This small room is more or less just the roof top of the lighthouse
which houses the light.  A narrow walkway encircles the light, so
that regular maintenance can be performed.  Some shelves on the
walls hold tools and oils which keep the machinery in fine tune so
that no ships run afoul of the many rocks in this part of the ocean.

beachqq27@nwbeaches.title: Keeper's Playroom
beachqq27@nwbeaches.description:
This small ten by ten room once was a simple like the others which
connect to the Operating Room, however because of the nature of the
specimen which abides in this space, it has been spruced up just a
bit.  A huge bed dominates the ENTIRE room, pillows strewn everywhere
with lace and frills and all.

beachqq29@nwbeaches.title: Cell
beachqq29@nwbeaches.description:
This bleak cell hosts only an uncomfortable looking cot and small hole
in one corner for necessary functions.

beachqq26@nwbeaches.title: Lighthouse Keeper's Operating Room
beachqq26@nwbeaches.description:
You see all and more of what you saw from the staircase.  Four cells lie
in all cardinal directions, each with a whimpering human subject in it!
Diagrams cover the walls, notes jotted on many of them, all dealing with
one goal in mind - the creation of the perfect sexual companion!  It seems
the 'good Lighthouse Keeper' may be a bit more than everyone believes him
to be...

mobqq02@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ02
mobqq02@nwbeaches.examine: Dirty little bird, you wish you had a wrist-cannon (more fun).
mobqq02@nwbeaches.description: A seagull pokes about, looking for scraps.

mobqq06@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ06
mobqq06@nwbeaches.examine:
You're not sure what he is, how he came to be what he is now, and you're
not sure you want to know.
mobqq06@nwbeaches.description: A naked man stands, shockingly deformed.

mobqq02_1@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ02_1
mobqq02_1@nwbeaches.examine: Dirty little bird, you wish you had a wrist-cannon (more fun).
mobqq02_1@nwbeaches.description: A seagull pokes about, looking for scraps.

mobqq13@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ13
mobqq13@nwbeaches.examine: This creature is larger than a city block and older than the Gods themselves.
mobqq13@nwbeaches.description: With a tremendous blast of force, the Kracken lunges up from the water!

mobqq12_3@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ12_3
mobqq12_3@nwbeaches.description: A fisherman sits here, trying to imitate Takker as best he can.

mobqq00@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ00
mobqq00@nwbeaches.examine: Looks like every other pelican you've seen....
mobqq00@nwbeaches.description: A pelican is here, taking a break in the sun.

mobqq03@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ03
mobqq03@nwbeaches.examine:
'&+RAll I ever wanted was sexual fulfillment', &+Wthe Lighthouse Keeper
explains, '&+RI never intended to hurt anyone, it seems that this all
&+Rjust got a bit out of hand....'&+W
mobqq03@nwbeaches.description: The Lighthouse Keeper is here, looking unsure of what he should do about you being here.

mobqq02_3@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ02_3
mobqq02_3@nwbeaches.examine: Dirty little bird, you wish you had a wrist-cannon (more fun).
mobqq02_3@nwbeaches.description: A seagull pokes about, looking for scraps.

mobqq09@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ09
mobqq09@nwbeaches.examine:
Mostly mutt, but very friendly, this black dog looks like the stereo-
typical house-dog.
mobqq09@nwbeaches.description: Max, the Lighthouse Keeper's dog rests before the fire.

mobqq02_2@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ02_2
mobqq02_2@nwbeaches.examine: Dirty little bird, you wish you had a wrist-cannon (more fun).
mobqq02_2@nwbeaches.description: A seagull pokes about, looking for scraps.

mobqq12_2@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ12_2
mobqq12_2@nwbeaches.description: A fisherman sits here, trying to imitate Takker as best he can.

mobqq11@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ11
mobqq11@nwbeaches.examine:
It is said by many that Old Man Takker hasn't left this spot for over
twenty.  His disciples bring him any food he needs, and they say he
never sleeps - just fishes.
mobqq11@nwbeaches.description: Old man Takker sits here, fishing away his life.

mobqq04@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ04
mobqq04@nwbeaches.examine:
It looks as it it may be a man, but then, being that it is naked, you
can see that it is just a bit of both.
mobqq04@nwbeaches.description: A strange looking.. thing(?) is standing here, no expression on it's face at all.

mobqq07@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ07
mobqq07@nwbeaches.examine: It is not describable, simply not describable.
mobqq07@nwbeaches.description: The Perfect Companion lies stretched out on the bed, waiting to give pleasure.

mobqq12@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ12
mobqq12@nwbeaches.description: A fisherman sits here, trying to imitate Takker as best he can.

mobqq01@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ01
mobqq01@nwbeaches.examine: Cute little guy, even though he looks a bit slimy.
mobqq01@nwbeaches.description: A sea otter is here, basking in the warmth of the sun.

mobqq10@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ10
mobqq10@nwbeaches.examine:
Although she looks as if she must be at least fifteen or sixteen years
old, she still seems quite content with her dolls.  What a nice girl!
mobqq10@nwbeaches.description: The Lighthouse Keeper's Daughter is here, playing house.

mobqq05@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ05
mobqq05@nwbeaches.examine:
It looks as if she may have been a very beautiful woman at one time,
however she is now so covered in dirt and grime, it is hard to tell.
mobqq05@nwbeaches.description: A woman lies here on her cot, bruised, naked, and bleeding.

mobqq00_2@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ00_2
mobqq00_2@nwbeaches.examine: Looks like every other pelican you've seen....
mobqq00_2@nwbeaches.description: A pelican is here, taking a break in the sun.

mobqq01_1@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ01_1
mobqq01_1@nwbeaches.examine: Cute little guy, even though he looks a bit slimy.
mobqq01_1@nwbeaches.description: A sea otter is here, basking in the warmth of the sun.

mobqq00_1@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ00_1
mobqq00_1@nwbeaches.examine: Looks like every other pelican you've seen....
mobqq00_1@nwbeaches.description: A pelican is here, taking a break in the sun.

mobqq01_2@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ01_2
mobqq01_2@nwbeaches.examine: Cute little guy, even though he looks a bit slimy.
mobqq01_2@nwbeaches.description: A sea otter is here, basking in the warmth of the sun.

mobqq08@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ08
mobqq08@nwbeaches.examine:
Such a kind looking lady, I'm sure she'd let you stay to dinner
if you had the urge.
mobqq08@nwbeaches.description: The Lighthouse Keeper's wife is here, sewing and humming a happy song.

mobqq12_1@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ12_1
mobqq12_1@nwbeaches.description: A fisherman sits here, trying to imitate Takker as best he can.

mobqq12_4@nwbeaches.name: mobQQ12_4
mobqq12_4@nwbeaches.description: A fisherman sits here, trying to imitate Takker as best he can.
